Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.12,0:00:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're all intellectual enough\Nin this audience at 4:30 to intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.63,0:00:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,instantly sees it. Positionality is a\Nfalsehood. The difference between hot
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.24,0:00:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and cold as you can see is an art\Nartificial positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.80,0:00:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So your intellect sees it. But no, the\Nproblem's going to be emotional that you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.60,0:00:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,get grim satisfaction out of everything.\NGrim satisfaction
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.16,0:00:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,out of martyrdom, out of being wronged.\NThe more horribly you're wronged, let me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.80,0:00:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,tell you, the bigger the juice,\Nthe more horrible the crime committed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.48,0:00:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,against you, the more stuck you are in\Nyour ego now
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.00,0:01:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because the payoff is big.\NThe payoff gets bigger and bigger. And
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.03,0:01:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as you evolve spiritually, the tempter\Nis going to come to you. And the way the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.19,0:01:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,tempter comes to you\Nis offering an enormous gratification of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.47,0:01:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a justified position\Nat a certain consciousness level. The
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.88,0:01:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,tempter comes to you. You might say that\Nwhich we call quote the tempter and the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.96,0:01:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,quote is present at all times and you're\Nreally constantly under the you're
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.56,0:01:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly under the test of the tempter\Nif you want to call it that. What's the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.04,0:01:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,source of the tempter? The source of the\Ntempter then is the pleasure one derives
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.07,0:01:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,out of one's ego positionalities.\NIt isn't power over others. It's the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.24,0:01:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,gratification you get out of power over\Nothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.00,0:02:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell do these idiots who\Nslaughter millions get out of it? They
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.52,0:02:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,don't even get to see it, right?\NHey, there's millions of people being
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.43,0:02:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,slaughtered and chopped up out there and\Nand you don't even get to see it. You're
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.72,0:02:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,locked up in your office here.\NLook what you're missing. Get out there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.56,0:02:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and slash around in the blood and step\Nover the bodies. I mean, you're missing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.12,0:02:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the grim satanic satisfaction.\NNo, the satisfaction he's getting out of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.40,0:02:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it is luciferic, not satanic.\NSatanic is the expression. But what he's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.76,0:02:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of is power over others.\NCapacity to be God over others. That's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.92,0:02:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Melissa. Look at his Look at him on TV.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.44,0:02:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The pridefulness of that positionality\Nis what he's unwilling to relinquish to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.20,0:02:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,God.\NYeah. And that's how you choose the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.95,0:02:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,lower astral\Npositionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.20,0:03:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right? So you'll you'll catch the\Nego red-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.44,0:03:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see that it gets a grim. You'll\Nsay, "Oh, I can't possibly be enjoying
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.15,0:03:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,this suffering." No, you're not enjoying\Nthe suffering. You're enjoying the juice
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.15,0:03:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you're getting out of the suffering. Get\Nwhat I'm saying by juice? The ego feeds
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.51,0:03:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,off the juice that it gets out of\Nwhat otherwise at least to the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.92,0:03:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is described as negative.\NNo sooner
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.48,0:03:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is the town demolished by the flowing\Nlava than they're rebuilding a new one
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.44,0:03:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly in the same place. Is that\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.04,0:03:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No. No sooner does the house slide down\Nthe side of the mountain into the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.56,0:03:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Pacific Ocean, then they're building a\Nnew one. Exactly the same place. No
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.00,0:03:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,sooner do the rivers\Nflow over the banks in the Midwest and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.20,0:04:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,sweep millions of houses away, they're\Ninstantly building houses as soon as the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.31,0:04:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,mud dries. The ego's\Nattraction and addiction is to the juice
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.64,0:04:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it gets out of suffering and being\Nmistreated.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.72,0:04:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the juice\Nof the far-left political liberal
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.04,0:04:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,correct politically correct position is\Nyou can get juice out of any social
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.16,0:04:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,reality\Nby recontextual re recontextualing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.60,0:04:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because the egotism involved\Nbrings you to a position called
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.52,0:04:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,entitlement.\NOnce you're entitled, everything is an
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.80,0:04:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,offense.\NEverything is an offense.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.75,0:04:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is a possible lawsuit.\NEverything is publicity
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.12,0:04:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because entitlement then is the\Ngrandiosity of the ego of the infant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.32,0:05:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So egoomania is nothing but the\Ngrandiosity of the unbridled infant of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.47,0:05:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego\Nexpecting the world to acknowledge it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.52,0:05:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The king baby inside expects the world\Nto cater to its egocentric position.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.88,0:05:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the ego the world never heard of\Nyou. And after you've left, it's not
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.32,0:05:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,going to miss you. And the idea that\Nit's going to cater to you while you're
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.56,0:05:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,here is about a three-month-old\Npositionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.47,0:05:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But the juice is derived out of the\Nindignities and injustices of this
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.80,0:05:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,world. It thrives on\Nall the people that are rude to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.19,0:05:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No sooner did they catch this crazy\Nbutcher of 30 people who chops them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.03,0:05:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wouldn't even tell you it's\Nunspeakable what he did to the remnants
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.00,0:05:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of their bodies.\NNo sooner does this happen than some
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.12,0:05:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,poppyccock jumps up on TV. He's worried\Nabout the civil rights of the sufferer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.52,0:06:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.03,0:06:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because he he can milk injustice\Nout of this. You can see the position of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.47,0:06:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the winner is always the bad guy. Like\Nthe capitalist is always the bad guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.84,0:06:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,right?\NWho says that? A guy wearing clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.31,0:06:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Where did you get your clothes?\NWell, it was manufactured by some
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.96,0:06:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,company. Where did the company get his\Nmoney? got it from capital, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.24,0:06:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You're walking on a sidewalk. Who made\Nthat sidewalk? Some company made the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.36,0:06:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,sidewalk. You sit in a car. Who made\Nyour car? You open your bottle of milk
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.24,0:06:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in the morning. Where'd you get the\Nmilk? You got it from some company.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.75,0:06:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Where'd you get the money to buy all\Nthese things that that the people you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.40,0:06:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,hate provided for you? Well, you got it\Nfrom the people who hate you hate
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.12,0:06:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because they provided the jobs, right?\NSo, you see how positionality makes
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.12,0:06:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,everything wrong. You know, you can make\Nthe goo goose who lays the golden egg
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.40,0:07:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the bad guy. So, positionality swinging\Nback and forth and creates the political
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.63,0:07:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,spectrum which keeps us entertained.\NEverybody,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.72,0:07:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,all the guys in the restaurant in the\Nmorning look forward to opening the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.44,0:07:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,editorial page. You know, they're all\Nset to go. You know what's today's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.91,0:07:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,outrageous calamity that you can really\Ndiscuss with the other guys and how
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.59,0:07:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,stupid the government is and all. So we\Nlove when you're honest about it. You
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.68,0:07:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,see that you love your ego. You love the\Njuice you get out of your ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.40,0:07:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,See once you admit that truth you've\Ntaken the cover off of it. You love the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.40,0:07:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,ego.\NIt's your source of juice. It's a source
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.40,0:07:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of all the injustices, the calamities,\Nthe pains, the hatreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.00,0:07:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Where would you be without it?\NYou'd be stuck with the reality of the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.63,0:08:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,self,\Nwhich doesn't buy that crap. Doesn't buy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.00,0:08:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it at all.\NGive me a break. That's that's what God
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.63,0:08:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,says when you say, "What you got to say\Ntoday, God? Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.08,0:08:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a break. Get enough from all\Nthis human juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Take away the TV set." I looked at it\Nand you're going to have it back. I gave
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.19,0:08:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,God a TV set and he said, "I don't want\Nto look at anymore. It's horrible."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.12,0:08:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because it's full of all this juice\Nthat we get out of it. The movies juice
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.15,0:08:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you to death. You know if you if you\Ncalibrate a lot of uh commercials, TV
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.15,0:08:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,commercials and a lot of movies, you\Nknow, your mind will go weak about 14
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.68,0:08:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,times a minute.\NWhy? Because we love the fear. We love
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.95,0:08:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the indignation. We love the shock.\NSo the way to undo the ego then is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.00,0:08:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,radical honesty.\NThe way of adida is radical truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.36,0:09:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to let go illusions\Nincluding the illusions about illusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.72,0:09:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of the ego then is the juice\Nthat we continuously get out of it which
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.95,0:09:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,pumps it up. Pumps it up. Pumps it up.\NGives it life. The willingness to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.00,0:09:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,relinquish that. That's what you have to\Nsurrender to God. Not the positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.27,0:09:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the minute you let go, the\Nsecondary gain you're getting out of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.44,0:09:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that position, the ego, the\Npositionality will disappear of itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.95,0:09:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll laugh at it.\NIt will let go of itself. So the thing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.16,0:09:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the thing to search for is what kind of\Nsatisfaction do I get out of that? I get
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.56,0:09:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the satisfaction of being wronged.\NWronged is wonderful, isn't it? Whole
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.80,0:09:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,countries go to war and they're wrong.\NThey're they're writing the wrong of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.68,0:10:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Versailles. What wrong of Versailles?\NThe Kaiser did the same thing Hitler did
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.88,0:10:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and lost. Now Hitler says, "Well, that\Nwas an injustice." What injustice?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.80,0:10:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody asked the Kaiser to invade Europe\Nand kill people, did they? No. All
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.76,0:10:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,right. So, it feeds off that injustice.\NThe whole German people
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.44,0:10:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,40 million people died in World War II.\NI was in World War II and it's more of a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.83,0:10:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,reality to me than many younger people.\NIt was a reality in which 70 million
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.07,0:10:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,people died\Nout of the juice out of the juice of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.72,0:10:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,being wrong. That was the juice of the\NNational Socialist Party, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.72,0:10:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It was going to write the wrong of\NVersailles and that justified everything
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.56,0:10:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,they did\Njust as bin Laden tries to juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.72,0:11:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's justified for the have nots to to\Nhate the hat the halves. That's the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.27,0:11:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,politicalization of it. Vinl is not a\Nhave not. He's a multi-millionaire
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.00,0:11:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which tends to diminish one's credence\Nand that positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.64,0:11:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. The pleasure that one gets\Nout of the juice of the ego justifies
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.56,0:11:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,everything. It justifies mass murder,\Ngenocide,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.68,0:11:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,if allowed to. The final killer bomb, if\Nthey lost the war, the final killer bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.39,0:11:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was big enough to to eliminate all of\Nmankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.72,0:11:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All of mankind was going to be\Neliminated by the final killer bomb if
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.44,0:11:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Russia lost a nuclear war with the\NUnited States. Luckily, there were
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.51,0:11:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,enough Russians to stop them before it\Nbecame a reality. But the megalomania
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.32,0:12:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,behind it, as you see, is unstoppable.\NThe difficulty with the reasonable ego
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.27,0:12:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of the western world is it presumes that\Nother people are going to operate with
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.36,0:12:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the law lawful confines and\Nreasonableness of the ego. Other people
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.04,0:12:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,are not other people totally disregard.\NPeople say, "Well, he wouldn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.20,0:12:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It would cost them all his countrymen."\NOh, of course he'd do that. The fact
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.00,0:12:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that he cost them all his countrymen\Nis cool man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.88,0:12:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill them all.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.20,0:12:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the weakness of our position as you see\Nit in the world is the presumption by
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.56,0:12:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the naive that other people are going to\Nbe ruled by reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.20,0:12:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,People in this room are the ones who are\Nmost vulnerable to that. The 400s is the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.12,0:12:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,level of reason. We say, "Well, nobody\Ndo that. That's irrational." Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.27,0:12:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's lots of people in the world that\Nthink that rationality is stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.00,0:13:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want something, you take it, man.\NWhat's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.76,0:13:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's whole cultures. And you know how\Nthat culture thinks?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.24,0:13:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she left her purse there, so she\Ndeserves it. I treat them all week long.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.27,0:13:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Monday, Wednesday, Friday, morning.\NWell, she deserves She left her purse
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.95,0:13:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,there. Of course, I stole it. What do\Nyou expect? I mean, you're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.16,0:13:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a different reality, right? Different\Nrules apply.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.76,0:13:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can get away with it, they deserved\Nit. Is a justification.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.24,0:13:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We in the 400s, you don't buy that. But\Ndown in the lower part of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.12,0:13:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that's justified.\NThey they deserve to die because they're
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.60,0:13:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,killable.\NWhoa. You realize what that means when
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.36,0:13:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,people come from that space?\NBecause they're killable. That's why
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.76,0:14:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,they deserve to die.\NThe dinosaur doesn't need justification
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.63,0:14:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to eat the smaller animals. He kills it\Ncuz it's chewable. I guess
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.39,0:14:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,all right. So now you you understand a\Nlittle bit more about the ego. You don't
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.88,0:14:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have to be afraid of it. You have to be\Nhonest that it's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.00,0:14:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and that it owes its survival to to the\Npayoff it gets out of its positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.27,0:14:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The payoff, the way to get rid of it is\Nfirst be honest about it and admit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.51,0:14:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I enjoy\Nwhatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.04,0:14:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, am I willing to let that enjoyment\Ngo for some higher purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.32,0:14:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can only take the word of\Npeople who have done so whether the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.76,0:14:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,sacrifice is worth it because it does\Nseem to the ego to sacrifice all of that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.63,0:15:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,glory and fame and justification and\Nrevenge and all is a big sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.80,0:15:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't kid yourself to the ego. It is a\Nbig sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.56,0:15:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a big sacrifice\Nto let go being right to let go
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.76,0:15:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,not nurturing that wrong to let go of\Nthat hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.56,0:15:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a big sacrifice. Don't pretend\Nit's a small sacrifice. There's a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.63,0:15:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,pseudo non-genuine spiritual work that\Npeople attempt and it doesn't work. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.48,0:15:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're unwilling to face the\Nnitty-gritty the nitty-gritty facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.68,0:15:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Radical truth means you got to take the\Nmask off everything and be willing to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.83,0:15:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,see it for what it is and now handle it\Nfrom the viewpoint of emotional honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.75,0:15:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a big massive payoff\Nand ego positions or you wouldn't be
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.75,0:16:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting here in a body today.\NYou would have karmically gone off into
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.80,0:16:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the midst of the higher realms.\NAnd therefore the fact that one is back
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.88,0:16:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,here in a body again means that one has\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.92,0:16:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,sold out spiritual truth for the\Ngratifications of the ego over and over
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.60,0:16:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,again. But in this lifetime it's coming\Nup to be questioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.51,0:16:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In this lifetime you say was it worth\Nit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.95,0:16:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the pres the experience of the\Npresence of God worth sacrificing all
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.92,0:16:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that I get out of my ego? The answer can\Nonly be accept only be gotten by faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.16,0:16:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually\Nexperientially no. Experientially you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.19,0:16:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,got nothing upon which to to say that\Ngiving it up would be a better deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.07,0:16:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything in your experience telling you\Nthat giving up the pleasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.16,0:16:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,resentments, and hatreds and\Nsatisfactions of winning
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.92,0:17:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is worth it?\NNot experientially. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.00,0:17:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith. Yes. Fa based on faith. based on\Nthis on the teaching of some
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.88,0:17:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,entity who's gone through the whole trip\Nand tells you that the end result
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.91,0:17:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,experience of God is so incredible\Nbeyond all description. So, so beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.00,0:17:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the totality of\Nall the values of all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.88,0:17:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout of all history,\Nall the pleasures and all the values and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.84,0:17:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,all the acquisitions emotionally and\Nmaterially of all of mankind throughout
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.79,0:17:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,all history\Nare like a speck compared to the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.60,0:17:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of God. Nothing is even in the\Nsame domain. Therefore, you're asked to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.67,0:17:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sacrifice that with which you're\Nfamiliar
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.88,0:17:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the hopes of entering a different\Ndomain
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.84,0:18:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and in that domain you have only have\Nthe traveler who's been there. Marco
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.08,0:18:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Polo tells you what the Chinese are like\Nbut you have to take his word for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.03,0:18:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So where the we have the inspiration\Nthen of the spiritual teacher. The value
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.44,0:18:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of the guru is primarily one of\Ncommitment to absolute truth out of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.32,0:18:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which comes an integrity which is so\Nprofound and convincing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.64,0:18:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that one buys that integrity.\NYou see truth cannot be argued. It
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.24,0:18:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be defended and it has no answers\Nfor any argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.24,0:18:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Its authority is absolute.\NIt is the absoluteness of the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.67,0:18:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that defies any question and against\Nwhich any question falls flat because
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.16,0:18:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no room for question. That\Nwhich is all that is is beyond all
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.40,0:18:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,questioning.\NTo let go and surrender the known for
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.28,0:19:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the unknown.\NWe call it the Institute for Advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.28,0:19:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual Research.\NEvery spiritual aspirant is a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.32,0:19:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,researcher. You have no idea what you're\Nreally going to experience when you let
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.96,0:19:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain thing go. You only find it by\Ndoing it. You only find it by doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.32,0:19:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the explorer,\Nyou can go by the compass, but you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.28,0:19:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,really know till you get there that\Nthat's an absolute fact. So each one of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.48,0:19:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,us evolves based on faith. The faith of\Nthe conviction of the integrity of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.88,0:19:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever spiritual teacher or church or\Nspiritual tradition,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.60,0:19:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever guru, whatever\None's inner direction leads one to that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.03,0:19:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which\Nyou're able to hang on to with absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.96,0:19:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,certainty.\NWhen I was an atheist, I already got the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.44,0:20:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute certainty of the truth of the\NBuddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.88,0:20:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I was an atheist at the time and I knew\Nthat what he said was absolutely so.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.40,0:20:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the intuitive knowingness was there\Nmany years prior to the validation
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.84,0:20:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,experientially.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.55,0:20:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That leads us up to the next uh topic\Nwhich we'll discuss after lunch because
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.00,0:20:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a heavy one and I don't want you to\Nbe hungry when we talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.12,0:20:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to explore what part does karma\Nplay in all this. Huh? Because
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.64,0:20:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego, the mechanisms of the ego, the\Npositionalities,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.88,0:20:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what we calibrate as of today as a group\Nand the kind of things we talk about and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.55,0:20:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,are valid to us today\Nto avoid the whole subject of karma is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.60,0:20:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,again the fallacy of many religious\Npositions who say I don't believe in
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.32,0:21:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,karma. I don't want anybody to believe\Nin karma at all. I don't want anybody to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.64,0:21:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,believe in karma. I don't believe in\Nkarma.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.32,0:21:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma is what you are.\NYou ask, "How do you let go of the ego?"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.48,0:21:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the ego is the accumulated karma\Nof all of life, through all of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.28,0:21:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,through all of history as it presents\Nitself now and the reality of that which
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.76,0:21:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you are at this moment.\NHe says, "I don't believe in karma." And
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.84,0:21:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,they tell you then in that case you\Ndon't exist because you got two ears,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.15,0:21:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,two eyes and a nose and a mouth. That\Nain't karmic. What is it? I mean you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.40,0:21:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't come up with four ears and three\Neyes and two mouths, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.84,0:21:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So obviously\Nat this moment then represents the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.12,0:21:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,accumulated energies and effects in form\Nthroughout all of time. You can't
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.32,0:22:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,pretend that somehow the evolution of\Nconsciousness throughout all time
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.60,0:22:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all forms of life has somehow\Nbypassed you and you have magically
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.32,0:22:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,escaped karma. No way.\NThat's a spiritual pride to think that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.32,0:22:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,one is not subject to the laws of the\Nuniverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.88,0:22:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,One time and then we'll have lunch. one\Ntime in a very advanced state. It was a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.44,0:22:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,very very advanced state came the down\Nthe potential downfall of the guru. A
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.00,0:22:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of gurus fall down\Nat the pass was over 800 820 840 860 850
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.48,0:22:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,around 850. All right. So uh\Nit's another shocking fact you see to be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.12,0:22:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a radical realist takes a lot of uh\Nguts. Takes a lot of guts and it takes a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.20,0:22:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of heart.\NUm, you got to face radical facts about
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.00,0:22:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,things you don't want to face. Many\Nwell-known gurus, if you calibrate their
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.79,0:23:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,writings, they're pretty pretty good.\NAnd if you calibrate where they were at
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.76,0:23:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at the height of their spiritual\Nevolution, you get a very good number.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.03,0:23:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you ask where they are at now,\Nyou may get a very low number. Shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.00,0:23:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because at each point along the way,\Nit's like a test comes up that says,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.15,0:23:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, yeah.\NAnd um
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.20,0:23:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the students I teach, I want them\Nprepared for that. First of all, don't
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.79,0:23:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,pretend it's not going to happen because\Nit's going to happen. When you say, "I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.24,0:23:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,never going to so and so again," the\Nnext question that comes up in the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.96,0:23:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,universe is, "Oh, yeah.\NOh, yeah. Uh-huh. Yeah, sure." Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.64,0:23:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway, this this was a very advanced\Nstate and um it was a state of absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.12,0:23:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,purity and\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.79,0:24:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,profound state of the presence\Nas clarity, peace and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.96,0:24:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,non-positionality.\NAnyway, in this state
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.52,0:24:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,which was nonverbal because thought had\Nstopped years before that came a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.12,0:24:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness presented itself. The\Nknowingness was
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.48,0:24:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,now that you have transcended karma, you\Nknow, are no longer answerable to some
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.24,0:24:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,otherness call God.\NAnd you realize there is no otherness to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.91,0:24:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which you are answerable for.\NAnd because you realize you're beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.48,0:24:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,all human karma,\Nyou're not answerable in human terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.72,0:24:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All power resides in you. Own it. That\Nwas the temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.60,0:24:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate lucatur\Npower for its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.88,0:24:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And the rationale was correct up to a\Ncertain level.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.52,0:25:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When you truly transcend the ego, you're\Nnot subject to human karma and normal
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.48,0:25:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,human karmic terms.\NNor is there some angry god that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.03,0:25:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,going to face who's going to get even\Nwith you for being bad and beat you up
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.15,0:25:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and throw you into hell. All that's\NSo anyway, you've transcended
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.52,0:25:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,all that. Now knowing all that, how\Nabout this baby? You are the power.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.32,0:25:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There comes the luciferic temptation.\NAnd you could see who had said yes and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.96,0:25:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,who had said no.\NIt was strange. Not all that many been
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.52,0:25:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,through. And you could see who said yes\Nand who said no.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.84,0:25:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh power for its own sake. You say to\Nyourself, why would that which is called
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.55,0:25:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we call evil by the world's terms, why\Nwould it choose to be that way? It does
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.00,0:25:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it for the payoff\Nfor the sake of power itself. Not
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.79,0:26:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because the power gets you something but\Nfor its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.84,0:26:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as people were murdered, not for\Nsome motive, looking for psychological
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.60,0:26:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,reasons why the thrill killer kills is\Nreally absurd. Got beat up in his
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.79,0:26:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,childhood. Yeah, right. Everybody got\Nbeat up in his childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.40,0:26:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he does it for the sake of it\Nitself. He murdered for the sake of the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.03,0:26:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,thrill of murdering. All right. So the\Npayoff, the way we surrender the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.15,0:26:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then is we're radically honest. We're\Nradically honest. We see the payoff we
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.96,0:26:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,get out of it. We're radically honest\Nabout whether we're actually willing to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.96,0:26:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,give up that payoff for something\Npromised but not yet experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.60,0:26:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is that takes faith.\NAll right. So that sort of answers
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.32,0:26:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the questions that that came up\Nand we will talk more about karma
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.91,0:26:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because there are questions there about\Nit. What is it really? Uh how far does
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.27,0:27:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it go?\NYou see the error that was made by that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.60,0:27:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,luciferic energy at that level was it's\Ntrue you're beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.40,0:27:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the karma of the ego\Nbut you are not beyond the karma of the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.40,0:27:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,reality of the universe.\NYou're not beyond the reality of the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.03,0:27:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,karma of God of the reality of the\Nuniverse which is far beyond the human
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.48,0:27:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and includes you in it brother.\NSo if I know what to say to that entity
