Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.88,0:30:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,verbalization is not possible in that\Ndivine state of bliss
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.60,0:30:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To understand spiritual work, it's it's\Nnecessary to know something about karma
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.44,0:30:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nwhat is the truth of karma? What does it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.88,0:30:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,really mean?\NFirst of all, it's somewhat stigmatized
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.84,0:30:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,amongst Christian circles and others as\Nbeing of eastern origin and therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.52,0:30:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,foreign and all this and that.\Nuh karma as a specific religious concept
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.96,0:30:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of course is defined in the dictionary\Nin a very specific way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.76,0:30:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma in my understanding is more the\Nessence of karma
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.24,0:30:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in that all that is the entire universe\Nin fact all the universes of universes
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.91,0:30:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is one karmic\Ntotality
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.91,0:31:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,one karmic symphony\Nin other words all that ever existed all
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.55,0:31:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that ever\Nis in thought word or deed
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.84,0:31:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in both the linear and the nonlinear\Ndomains
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.48,0:31:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,are part of a total oneness.\NTo be beyond karma would mean the you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.12,0:31:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that somehow you've escaped the oneness\Nof the totality of God and all the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.88,0:31:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,universes which is not likely.\NThe universe is one
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.64,0:31:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic um\Nunity
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.76,0:31:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in perfect and total balance in every\Ndetail.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.32,0:31:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All that is is obviously part of the\Nevolution of all that was at the point
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.44,0:32:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of observation becoming\Nthe fulfillment of its
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.84,0:32:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,innate propensity\Nwhich was created as part of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.79,0:32:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is perfect because at every\Npoint it is fulfilling its potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.36,0:32:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is possible for that potentiality\Nto unfold under the conditions that we
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.48,0:32:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,call the present and the next instant it\Nwill again be perfect. So all is perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.76,0:32:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,at every instant.\NThe only way to make it not perfect is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.67,0:32:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to\Ncontextualize it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.60,0:32:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in the hypothetical.\NBut because the hypothetical has no
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.72,0:32:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,reality, it does not invalidate the\Ntruth of what was just said. The
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.15,0:33:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,hypothetical does not exist.\NM
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.24,0:33:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so because the universe is one karmic\Nunity
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.51,0:33:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Na continuous state of perfection of the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.67,0:33:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,unfolding of its potentiality.\NNothing can escape karma and still be
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.39,0:33:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,part of the universe. So if anything was\Nbeyond karma, you wouldn't know about
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.64,0:33:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NSo there's no point to worry about it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.32,0:33:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because you wouldn't you wouldn't exist.\NNeither would you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.91,0:33:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot be anything this instant\Nunless you were something the last
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.44,0:33:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,instant. Right? Okay.\NHow does it operate really spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.67,0:33:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,speaking? First of all, the confusion\Nhas to do with um confusing karma with
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.60,0:33:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,reincarnation. The reason it's rejected\Nby Christian uh belief systems is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.00,0:33:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because of two things. that Jesus Christ\Ndid not talk about it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.60,0:34:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and specifically\Nit's referring to embodiment. Embodiment
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.08,0:34:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,generally karma is understood by the\Ncommon layman as
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.35,0:34:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,uh if you're not good you'll become back\Nas a toad or you were a very good toad
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.04,0:34:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you're not a toad anymore.\NSo it's confused with incarnation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.76,0:34:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma and incarnation are two different\Nthings.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.52,0:34:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Reincarnation can be a karmic\Npotentiality or it may not.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.20,0:34:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma is merely stating that that which\Nis continuous is continuous and part of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.63,0:34:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,an ongoing oneness.\NWhat it really what it's really saying
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.00,0:34:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually is that\NThe decisions of the spiritual will
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.87,0:35:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which is really what determines karma\Nkarma in the true meaning of the sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.88,0:35:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The decisions of the spiritual will then\Nhave consequences. Consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.20,0:35:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,These consequences are agreed upon by\Nall religions. Those who claim they
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.07,0:35:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,don't believe in karma, of course they\Nbelieve in karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.76,0:35:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, why would you avoid sin?\NBecause after you die, karmically,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.44,0:35:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to go to other places. So,\Nthey all believe in karma, but they
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.96,0:35:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,don't believe in reincarnation. That's\Ntwo different things. Karma means that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.68,0:35:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the consequences of actions\Nwill have an effect in the future. And
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.96,0:35:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, Christ taught that you reap\Nas you sow, etc. So he taught karma but
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.68,0:35:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,he did not get into the whole problem of\Nembodiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.80,0:36:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmically embodiment is a very\Ncomplicated and tricky question. It may
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.32,0:36:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,or may not occur and it may or not be an\Noption and it may or may not be uh said
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.64,0:36:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,yes to. The other thing that people\Ndon't understand about karma is that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.11,0:36:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an infinite\Nan infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.32,0:36:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,number of universes. There's an infinite\Nnumber of domains and within an infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.24,0:36:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,number of domains there's an infinite\Npotentiality of inf infinite universes
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.11,0:36:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and these multiply at at an infinite\Nrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.83,0:36:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now once you wrap yourself around that\None,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.96,0:36:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to ask a question that's been\Nbugging me. May I ask this question? I
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.20,0:36:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,may ask this question.\NJesus Christ never had any previous
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.76,0:36:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,physical incarnations.\NI may ask that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.28,0:37:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a fact. It's just the Buddha\Ndid. Just that's what I thought. I was
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.48,0:37:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,driving along the other day and I\Nthought one reason Jesus Christ didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.20,0:37:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about previous embodiment is\Nbecause they never had any.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.96,0:37:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha however did\Nand they at about level 600 you recall
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.28,0:37:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,them. Not that they're a different\Nlifetime but it's just like a memory
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.32,0:37:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,like you remember\Nwhat your teacher said in 8th grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.07,0:37:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jesus Christ first of all came\Ndirectly from heaven. See, never
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.59,0:37:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,incarnated as a physicality, as a human\Nphysicality. Jesus Christ never
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.56,0:37:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,incarnated as a physicality before\Nresist.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.88,0:37:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh. I didn't know that. Well, that's\None thing I like about kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.35,0:37:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask these questions and after you've\Nasked thousands of them, it weaves a
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.64,0:37:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,fabric of understanding\Nthat um
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.11,0:38:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is greater in depth and dimension and\Nand subtly than can be usually
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.40,0:38:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,described.\NI always thought until this moment that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.40,0:38:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ didn't go into the subject\Nof karma specifically past life karma
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.00,0:38:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is because\Nthe ego as it is today is the karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.88,0:38:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Your karma is today's ego. Today's ego\Nis the compilation of all that's
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.80,0:38:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,occurred in the evolution of this\Nconsciousness up to this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.48,0:38:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like a tomato is\Nthis tomato sitting here represents the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.48,0:38:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of tomatoeness throughout all\Nof time until it is manifesting as this
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.04,0:38:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,tomato. There's no way this tomato can\Nescape tomato karma because it is tomato
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.80,0:38:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,karma. All right. So the ego of today is\Nnothing but the crystallization and
