Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.60,1:16:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,importance\Num how can you how can you um verify the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.76,1:16:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,validity of your findings uh such I\Nsuppose in kinesiology or whatever or in
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.96,1:16:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,one's work.\NThat's sort of the hypothetical asking
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.04,1:16:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the hypothetical. So, it's not really\Nanswerable in a radical logical way. Uh
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.28,1:16:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but\Nsub
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.71,1:17:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of one existence is\Npurely subjective
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.19,1:17:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and there is no escape from the from\Nsubjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.36,1:17:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So to ask somebody for what might be\Nconsidered objective from a certain
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.52,1:17:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectual hypothetical viewpoint\Ndoesn't really have any reality even if
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.92,1:17:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it was answerable\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.67,1:17:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of myself Susan and the\Naudience simultaneously is that we use a
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.52,1:17:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,certain technique to verify the yes or\Nno of various things but to some degree
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.32,1:17:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we already know the answer and all we're\Nlooking for is some external
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.76,1:17:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,verification for the purpose of\Ndemonstration really and for showing how
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.15,1:17:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,this technique can be used to further\Nspiritual progress and gain access to
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.76,1:17:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,information. Don't forget the\Ninformation that we talk about in these
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.12,1:17:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,lectures and write about etc. Most of it\Nhas never been known in the history of
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.28,1:17:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind. Not known certainly in a\Nverifiable way. uh maybe some sheaman
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.48,1:18:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,had a dream vision of it or somebody had\Na hallucination of it but nobody has
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.04,1:18:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,really contextualized it in a totally\Ncomprehensible way so as to make it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.88,1:18:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,assimilable and um verifiable.\NSo I think the value of what we uh do is
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.23,1:18:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you see if you get an answer that's\Noutside the expected realm or outside of
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.23,1:18:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,even the possible the outside of\Npossibility it requires an explanation
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.15,1:18:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and occasionally we get an outrageous\Nresponse. Well it doesn't mean the
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.19,1:18:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,response is wrong. It means that you\Ndon't comprehend it. A lot of times you
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.92,1:18:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,have to completely rephrase the\Nquestion.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.19,1:18:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The uh sometimes the question is already\Nbegging the answer and you'll get a
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.84,1:18:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,refusal.\NUh it's funny but consciousness is
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.56,1:18:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely bright.\NAnd uh we'll outsmart when you think
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.76,1:19:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're outsmarting it, you find you\Ndidn't get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.40,1:19:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And many a time we did it one time in\Nfront of an audience when and I've cited
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.48,1:19:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,this example before when we asked uh\NCarl Young's uh energy is over 520 and
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.71,1:19:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we got to know well we've done it\Nhundreds of times I know what Carl
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.92,1:19:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Young's energy is and she couldn't\Nunderstand it and I couldn't understand
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.08,1:19:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it well we said it is well he's dead so\Nit couldn't be could it said no when we
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.08,1:19:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,said it was we got a yes so just\Nphrasing one word Carl Young is over
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.08,1:19:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,520. Obvious the answer is no. But we\Nwere careless because we've answered
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.56,1:19:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that. We've asked that question so many\Ntimes. So you have to be careful how you
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.19,1:19:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,now the whole thing has to be internally\Nconsistent.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.67,1:19:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, if you spent a few weeks\Nwith us and saw us do hundreds and
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.48,1:19:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,hundreds of of things, you begin to see\Na fabric of truth form itself which is
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.04,1:20:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,internally consistent. Now, at this\Ntime,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.00,1:20:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we were going to sit this way and that\Nway. Maybe we should have set the other
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.48,1:20:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,way. Never mind. The main\Nafter at this time, I've done over
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.71,1:20:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,255,000 calibrations. 260,000 265,000\N270,000 275,000 280,000
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.40,1:20:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,290,000 over 300,000 calibrations over\N290,000 calibrations. 294
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.44,1:20:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,294,000 calibrations.\NWell, if you've looked at 294,000 rocks
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.64,1:20:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and examined them under a microscope,\Nyou begin to get a feeling for geology.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.60,1:20:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What shale and what ain't shale. I mean,\Nyou know, you begin to get what uh so
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.28,1:20:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,just the sheer experience of it, I\Nthink, is interesting. When I first saw
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.40,1:20:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology, I had already gone into\Nthat infinite paradigm we call nonlinear
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.71,1:20:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and which religiously is called the\Npresence of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.64,1:21:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I first saw it, I was already\Nseeing it from a different paradigm of
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.40,1:21:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,reality. The whole audience was within\Nthe linear
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.76,1:21:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Newtonian domain. What they saw was a\Nlocal phenomena and what I saw was a
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.28,1:21:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,non-local phenomena. We both witnessed\Nthe same event. To me it was obviously
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.80,1:21:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the answer uh the non-local answer of\Nthe nature coming from the nature of
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.04,1:21:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself\Nand the rest of the audience thought it
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.12,1:21:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,was the reaction of the body's\Nphysiology to a turnup
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.76,1:21:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you Some people thought well you know\Nthey presumed um
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.76,1:21:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was very clearly a nonlinear\Nimpersonal response. has nothing to do
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.15,1:22:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with the questioner. It had nothing to\Ndo with the
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.00,1:22:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,person of the who was uh was being the\Nsubject
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.67,1:22:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was obviously the connection\Nbetween the invisible nonlinear domain
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.48,1:22:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nuh the consciousness of mankind is
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.28,1:22:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,expresses itself through the nervous\Nsystem.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.40,1:22:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So in our cell was\Ninfinite non-local impersonal
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.52,1:22:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and was a response of consciousness\Nitself to the presence of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.15,1:22:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Italy we first we called it true versus\Nfalse but that is not correct and I
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.80,1:22:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,think in power versus force we said it\Nwas true versus false but in eye of the
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.71,1:22:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,eye we corrected that it's not true\Nversus tr false it's true versus not
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.56,1:22:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,true\Nthere is no opposite to truth
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.67,1:23:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,uh truth is either present or not if\Ntruth is present like u then you go
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.76,1:23:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,strong if truth is not present because\Nit has no existence. So non that which
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.15,1:23:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is not real has no existence.\NConsciousness therefore does not respond
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.40,1:23:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to it because it is only um belief\Nsystem in your head with no reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.71,1:23:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is no such thing in the\Nuniverse aseness.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.08,1:23:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's either yes or the absence of\Nyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.76,1:23:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a very profound spiritual\Nunderstanding
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.23,1:23:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because it destroys the artifact of the\Npolarity of the opposites
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.36,1:23:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and we use as the analogy of that when\Nyou throw the switch on electricity is
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.32,1:23:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,present in the wire.\NElectricity is either present or not
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.60,1:23:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,present. There is no condition known as\Noffness.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.84,1:24:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So the duality of the ego is that off\Nand on are opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.92,1:24:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no opposite to God. There is no\Nopposite to truth. There is no opposite
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.15,1:24:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to existence.\NSo when I hit the duality at age three
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.56,1:24:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and again later resolved at maybe age 60\Nof existence versus non-existence, the
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.52,1:24:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,fallacy of it made me laugh. There is\Nthere is only existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.76,1:24:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see the absurdity of asking\Nwhether or not non non-existence exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.80,1:24:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-existence is not an ab not an\Noption. Just like absence is not an
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.36,1:24:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,option. You see something is either\Npresent or not present. There is no
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.19,1:24:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,condition called absence. You know what\NI mean? We can't send absence into this
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.36,1:24:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,room and fill it up. After we all leave\Nhere, we'll send in absence. Absence is
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.36,1:25:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,not has no existence.\NYou either there's either hearness or
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.32,1:25:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,not heariness. But there is no such\Nthing as absence.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.88,1:25:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But the ego's belief in that which is\Nunreal is the cause of the human
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.84,1:25:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,dilemma. That there is an opposite to\NGod, that there is an opposite to
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.92,1:25:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,existence.\NThe nearest o not opposite the the
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.76,1:25:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,nearest thing to non-existence is\Noblivion
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.04,1:25:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's so to see that is to solve\Nthe ancient dilemma of the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.40,1:25:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,fallacy there's errors in all religions\Nand the one in Buddhism
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.56,1:25:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is the misunderstanding of the absolute\Ninfinite as void
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.15,1:25:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and in its mistransation The void\Nbecomes a state to be
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.48,1:25:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,desired\Nuh and achieved by the pathway of
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.12,1:26:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,negation.\NActually non-existence is not a
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.12,1:26:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,possibility.\NVoidness as nothingness is not a
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.60,1:26:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,possibility.\NVoidness is absence of form or content
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.76,1:26:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is the absolute reality. But if one\Nbelieves that the absolute reality
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.28,1:26:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to be achieved is the Buddha nature as\Nvoidness is though voidness is a
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.67,1:26:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,condition\Na reality condition
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.23,1:26:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,leads one uh into the state of the void\Nand when you leave the body you go into
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.15,1:26:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,oblivion.\NThen because that's not a reality you
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.48,1:26:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,can't stay in it.\Nbecause you can't stay in it. You find
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.92,1:26:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself back at age three in a little\Nwooden wagon wagon stunned by the fact
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.36,1:27:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that you exist again.\NThat's the fallacy of the Hinyana
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.67,1:27:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,pathway\Ncertain branch of the Hinyana pathway.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.40,1:27:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The misunderstanding\Nthat that which has no existence can
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.19,1:27:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,exist as non-existence. You see the\Nfallacy of it even within the realm of
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.00,1:27:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,logic.\NBut when spoken by a guru with gongs,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.44,1:27:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,shaved head, incense sitting on a tiger\Nrag, a tiger skin, one assumes this is
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.96,1:27:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the ultimate authority.\NOne worships it, deifies it, and not
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.63,1:27:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,become sought after. God is\Nnon-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.52,1:27:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an impossible coin. You cannot\Nget past that one
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.00,1:27:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,until\Nwhat do we say 850. At 8:50 you passed
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.96,1:27:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,into that doorway.\NThe purpose of all that is to try to uh
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.92,1:28:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,unhook the power of\Npositionality creating a duality which
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.08,1:28:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is the block to enlightenment.\NIf you see that only existence exists,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.08,1:28:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,if you see that only heat exists, if you\Nsee that in the supposed gradations
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.52,1:28:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,between light and darkness, there is\Nonly the one and that is light and that
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.71,1:28:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,darkness has no independent existence,\Nthen you're halfway to enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.15,1:28:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because those are the great obstacles.\NAny questions?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.44,1:28:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the 3x5 card.\N>> Ah,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.04,1:28:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,okay. Do you go\N>> consciousness is not personal? What does
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.88,1:29:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it mean? We earn the chance\Nfor better opportunities for for better
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.28,1:29:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,choices.\NIt's like consciousness is the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.67,1:29:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The field karma is still content.\NOne has not escaped content yet. To go
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.44,1:29:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond karma means to have escaped the\Nlimitation of content.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.92,1:29:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness\Nis infinite context.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.92,1:29:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no form\Nlike the sky.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.48,1:29:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma would be like a cloud has still\Nhas form.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.67,1:29:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It hangs loose within the sky.\NIt's within the sky.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.15,1:29:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So karma then would be the consequence\Nof one's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.84,1:29:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual decisions\Nhas an influence on the shape of the
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.15,1:30:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,cloud. But consciousness is like the\Nsky. The field of consciousness which is
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.48,1:30:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,impersonal is unaffected by the cloud.\NBut where the cloud goes in the sky will
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.76,1:30:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,depend on its shape, size, consistency,\Nhumidity, barometric pressure
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.28,1:30:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and many things. Yes.\NYou see in the meditative uh technique
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.48,1:30:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize the presence of God, one goes\Nback from
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.28,1:30:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,identifying with\Nthe content of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.56,1:30:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to the field in which\Nto the field itself to realize that I am
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.52,1:30:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,not the content of the mind.\NI am that uh upon which the mind is
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.67,1:30:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,playing.\NSee,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.71,1:31:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like I'm the receiver and not the\Nnotes of the music. The receiver remains
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.56,1:31:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the same no matter what music is playing\Non it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.52,1:31:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You all of a sudden jump from\Nidentifying with the content. I am those
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.63,1:31:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,thoughts, words, images and memories to\NI am that which empowers them to become
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.15,1:31:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,known.\NSo you become the knower of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.48,1:31:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You become the witness.\NYou become at a certain level the
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.00,1:31:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencer. Beyond the experiencer is\Nthe witness and the observer.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.23,1:31:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The witness and the observer. and the\Nexperiencer arise out of an impersonal
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.71,1:31:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,field. You can realize these things are\Nimpersonal because witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.52,1:31:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,witnessing and observing is not uh\Nwithin you. You cannot shut it on and
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.60,1:32:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,off at will. If it's who you were, you\Ncould shut it on and off, but it's not
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.52,1:32:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,who you are.\NBehind the witness observer experiencer
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.12,1:32:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is an impersonal allp prevailing field\Nof consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.96,1:32:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Even consciousness is not aware of its\Nown existence except uh for the field of
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.80,1:32:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness. So you you identify you stop\Nidentifying with the movie and you begin
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.96,1:32:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to see one can witness the movie only\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.67,1:32:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that upon which it is being projected as\Nformless.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.52,1:32:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin so you you withdraw your\Ninvestment in identification of self as
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.52,1:32:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,form and content of memory and\Nexperience.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.56,1:32:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You see yourself as that which is beyond\Nform.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.63,1:33:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That you are the field upon which form\Nreveals itself as form.
